70 /**
71  * As all parameters are passed from hoc as double, we need
72  * to calculate max integer that can fit into double variable.
73  *
74  * With IEEE 64-bit double has 52 bits of mantissa, so it's 2^53.
75  * calculating it with approach `while (dbl + 1 != dbl) dbl++;`
76  * has issues with SSE and other 32 bits platform. So we are using
77  * direct value here.
78  *
79  * The maximum mantissa 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFF which is 52 bits all 1.
80  * In Python it's:
81  *
82  * >>> (2.**53).hex()
83  * '0x1.0000000000000p+53'
84  * >>> (2.**53)
85  * 9007199254740992.0
86  *
87  * See https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1848700/biggest-integer-that-can-be-stored-in-a-double
88  */
89 static double dmaxint_ = 9007199254740992;

91 // Definitions allow machine independent write and read
92 // note that must include BYTEHEADER at head of routine
93 // The policy is that each machine vwrite binary information in
94 // without swapping, ie. native endian.
95 // On reading, the type is checked to decide whether
96 // byteswapping should be performed
97 
98 #define BYTEHEADER \
99  int _II__; \
100  char* _IN__; \
101  char _OUT__[16]; \
102  int BYTESWAP_FLAG = 0;
103 #define BYTESWAP(_X__, _TYPE__) \
104  if (BYTESWAP_FLAG == 1) { \
105  _IN__ = (char*) &(_X__); \
106  for (_II__ = 0; _II__ < sizeof(_TYPE__); _II__++) { \
107  _OUT__[_II__] = _IN__[sizeof(_TYPE__) - _II__ - 1]; \
108  } \
109  (_X__) = *((_TYPE__*) &_OUT__); \
110  }

219 /* the Vect->elem(start, end) function was used in about a dozen places
220 for the purpose of dealing with a subrange of elements. However that
221 function clones the subrange and returns a new Vect. This caused a
222 memory leak and was needlessly inefficient for those functions.
223 To fix both problems for these specific functions
224 we use a special vector which does not have
225 it's own space but merely a pointer and capacity to the right space of
226 the original vector. The usage is restricted to only once at a time, i.e.
227 can't use two subvecs at once and never do anything which affects the
228 memory space.
229 */

466  OcFile* f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);

492  break;
493  }
494

496  FRead(&(vp->elem(0)), sizeof(double), n, fp);
497  break;
498 
499  case 3: // floats
500  {
501  float* xf = (float*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(float));
502  FRead(xf, sizeof(float), n, fp);
503  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
504  vp->elem(i) = double(xf[i]);
505  }
506  free((char*) xf);
507  break;
508  }
509 
510  case 2: // unsigned short ints
511  {
512  unsigned short* xi = (unsigned short*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(unsigned short));
513  FRead(xi, sizeof(unsigned short), n, fp);
514  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
515  vp->elem(i) = double(xi[i]);
516  }
517  free((char*) xi);
518  break;
519  }
520

522  {

524  FRead(xc, sizeof(char), n, fp);

535 static double v_vwrite(void* v) {
536  Vect* vp = (Vect*) v;
537 
538  Object* ob = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
539  check_obj_type(ob, "File");
540  OcFile* f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);
541 
542  FILE* fp = f->file();
543  if (!fp) {
544  return 0.;
545  }
546 
547  BinaryMode(f)
548  // first, write the size of the vector
549  int n = vp->size();
550  FWrite(&n, sizeof(int), 1, fp);
551 
552  // next, write the type of elements
553  int type = 4;
554  if (ifarg(2)) {
555  type = int(chkarg(2, 1, 5));
556  }
557  FWrite(&type, sizeof(int), 1, fp);
558 
559  // convert the data if necessary
560  int i;
561  void* s;
562  const char* x;
563 
564  double min, max, r, sf, sub, intermed;
565  switch (type) {
566  case 5: // integers as ints (no scaling)
567  {
568  int* xi = (int*) malloc(n * sizeof(int));
569  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
570  xi[i] = (int) (vp->elem(i));
571  }
572  FWrite(xi, sizeof(int), n, fp);
573  free((char*) xi);
574  break;
575  }
576 
577  case 4: // doubles (no conversion unless BYTESWAP used and needed)
578  {
579  s = (void*) (&(vp->elem(0)));
580  x = (const char*) s;
581  FWrite(x, sizeof(double), n, fp);
582  break;
583  }
584 
585  case 3: // float (simple automatic type conversion)
586  {
587  float* xf = (float*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(float));
588  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
589  xf[i] = float(vp->elem(i));
590  }
591  FWrite(xf, sizeof(float), n, fp);
592  free((char*) xf);
593  break;
594  }
595 
596 
597  case 2: // short ints (scale to 16 bits with compression)
598  {
599  auto minmax = std::minmax_element(vp->begin(), vp->end());
600  min = *minmax.first;
601  max = *minmax.second;
602  r = max - min;
603  if (r > 0) {
604  sf = TWO_BYTE_HIGH / r;
605  } else {
606  sf = 1.;
607  }
608  unsigned short* xi = (unsigned short*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(unsigned short));
609  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
610  intermed = (vp->elem(i) - min) * sf;
611  xi[i] = (unsigned short) intermed;
612  }
613  s = (void*) xi;
614  x = (const char*) s;
615  // store the info needed to reconvert
616  FWrite(&sf, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
617  FWrite(&min, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
618  // store the actual data
619  FWrite(x, sizeof(unsigned short), n, fp);
620  free((char*) xi);
621  break;
622  }
623 
624  case 1: // char (scale to 8 bits with compression)
625  {
626  sub = ONE_BYTE_HALF;
627  auto minmax = std::minmax_element(vp->begin(), vp->end());
628  min = *minmax.first;
629  max = *minmax.second;
630  r = max - min;
631  if (r > 0) {
632  sf = ONE_BYTE_HIGH / r;
633  } else {
634  sf = 1.;
635  }
636 
637  char* xc = (char*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(char));
638  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
639  xc[i] = char(((vp->elem(i) - min) * sf) - sub);
640  }
641  s = (void*) xc;
642  x = (const char*) s;
643  // store the info needed to reconvert
644  FWrite(&sf, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
645  FWrite(&min, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
646  FWrite(x, sizeof(char), n, fp);
647  free(xc);
648  break;
649  }
650  }
651  return 1;
652 }

655 static double v_vread(void* v) {
656  Vect* vp = (Vect*) v;
657  void* s = (void*) (vp->data());
658 
659  Object* ob = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
660  check_obj_type(ob, "File");
661  OcFile* f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);
662  BYTEHEADER
663 
664  FILE* fp = f->file();
665  if (!fp) {
666  return 0.;
667  }
668 
669  BinaryMode(f) int n;
670  FRead(&n, sizeof(int), 1, fp);
671 
672  int type = 0;
673  FRead(&type, sizeof(int), 1, fp);
674 
675  // since the type ranges from 1 to 5 (very important that it not be 0)
676  // we can check the type and decide if it needs to be byteswapped
677  if (type < 1 || type > 5) {
678  BYTESWAP_FLAG = 1;
679  } else {
680  BYTESWAP_FLAG = 0;
681  }
682 
683  BYTESWAP(n, int)
684  BYTESWAP(type, int)
685  if (type < 1 || type > 5) {
686  return 0.;
687  }
688  if (vp->size() != n)
689  vp->resize(n);
690 
691  // read as appropriate type and convert to doubles
692 
693  int i;
694  double sf = 1.;
695  double min = 0.;
696  double add;
697 
698  switch (type) {
699  case 5: // ints; no conversion
700  {
701  int* xi = (int*) malloc(n * sizeof(int));
702  FRead(xi, sizeof(int), n, fp);
703  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
704  BYTESWAP(xi[i], int)
705  vp->elem(i) = double(xi[i]);
706  }
707  free((char*) xi);
708  break;
709  }
710 
711  case 4: // doubles
712  FRead(&(vp->elem(0)), sizeof(double), n, fp);
713  if (BYTESWAP_FLAG == 1) {
714  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
715  BYTESWAP(vp->elem(i), double)
716  }
717  }
718  break;
719 
720  case 3: // floats
721  {
722  float* xf = (float*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(float));
723  FRead(xf, sizeof(float), n, fp);
724  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
725  BYTESWAP(xf[i], float)
726  vp->elem(i) = double(xf[i]);
727  }
728  free((char*) xf);
729  break;
730  }
731 
732  case 2: // unsigned short ints
733  { // convert back to double
734  FRead(&sf, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
735  FRead(&min, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
736  BYTESWAP(sf, double)
737  BYTESWAP(min, double)
738 
739  unsigned short* xi = (unsigned short*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(unsigned short));
740  FRead(xi, sizeof(unsigned short), n, fp);
741  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
742  BYTESWAP(xi[i], short)
743  vp->elem(i) = double(xi[i] / sf + min);
744  }
745  free((char*) xi);
746  break;
747  }
748 
749  case 1: // char
750  { // convert back to double
751  FRead(&sf, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
752  FRead(&min, sizeof(double), 1, fp);
753  BYTESWAP(sf, double)
754  BYTESWAP(min, double)
755  char* xc = (char*) malloc(n * (unsigned) sizeof(char));
756  FRead(xc, sizeof(char), n, fp);
757  add = ONE_BYTE_HALF;
758  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
759  vp->elem(i) = double((xc[i] + add) / sf + min);
760  }
761  free(xc);
762  break;
763  }
764  }
765  return 1;
766 }

769 static double v_printf(void* v) {
770  Vect* x = (Vect*) v;
771 
772  int top = x->size() - 1;
773  int start = 0;
774  int end = top;
775  int next_arg = 1;
776  const char* format = "%g\t";
777  int print_file = 0;
778  int extra_newline = 1; // when no File
779  OcFile* f;
780 
781  if (ifarg(next_arg) && (hoc_is_object_arg(next_arg))) {
782  Object* ob = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
783  check_obj_type(ob, "File");
784  f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);
785  format = "%g\n";
786  next_arg++;
787  print_file = 1;
788  }
789  if (ifarg(next_arg) && (hoc_argtype(next_arg) == STRING)) {
790  format = gargstr(next_arg);
791  next_arg++;
792  extra_newline = 0;
793  }
794  if (ifarg(next_arg)) {
795  start = int(chkarg(next_arg, 0, top));
796  end = int(chkarg(next_arg + 1, start, top));
797  }
798 
799  if (print_file) {
800  for (int i = start; i <= end; i++) {
801  fprintf(f->file(), format, x->elem(i));
802  }
803  fprintf(f->file(), "\n");
804  } else {
805  for (int i = start; i <= end; i++) {
806  Printf(format, x->elem(i));
807  if (extra_newline && !((i - start + 1) % 5)) {
808  Printf("\n");
809  }
810  }
811  if (extra_newline) {
812  Printf("\n");
813  }
814  }
815  hoc_return_type_code = 1; // integer
816  return double(end - start + 1);
817 }

820 static double v_scanf(void* v) {
821  Vect* x = (Vect*) v;
822 
823  int n = -1;
824  int c = 1;
825  int nc = 1;
826  Object* ob = *hoc_objgetarg(1);
827  check_obj_type(ob, "File");
828  OcFile* f = (OcFile*) (ob->u.this_pointer);
829 
830  hoc_return_type_code = 1; // integer
831 
832  if (ifarg(4)) {
833  n = int(*getarg(2));
834  c = int(*getarg(3));
835  nc = int(*getarg(4));
836  } else if (ifarg(3)) {
837  c = int(*getarg(2));
838  nc = int(*getarg(3));
839  } else if (ifarg(2)) {
840  n = int(*getarg(2));
841  }
842 
843  if (n >= 0) {
844  x->resize(n);
845  } else if (x->size()) { // gnuvec legacy handling
846  x->resize(0);
847  }
848 
849  // start at the right column
850 
851  int i = 0;
852 
853  while ((n < 0 || i < n) && !f->eof()) {
854  // skip unwanted columns before
855  int j;
856  for (j = 1; j < c; j++) {
857  if (!f->eof())
858  hoc_scan(f->file());
859  }
860 
861  // read data
862  if (!f->eof()) {
863  if (n >= 0)
864  x->elem(i) = hoc_scan(f->file());
865  else
866  x->push_back(hoc_scan(f->file()));
867  }
868 
869  // skip unwanted columns after
870  for (j = c; j < nc; j++) {
871  if (!f->eof())
872  hoc_scan(f->file());
873  }
874 
875  i++;
876  }
877 
878  if (x->size() != i)
879  x->resize(i);
880 
881  return double(i);
882 }

1223 static Object** v_sumgauss(void* v) {
1224  Vect* x = (Vect*) v;
1225 
1226  double low = *getarg(1);
1227  double high = chkarg(2, low, 1e99);
1228  double step = chkarg(3, 1.e-99, 1.e99);
1229  double var = chkarg(4, 0, 1.e99);
1230  Vect* w;
1231  bool d = false;
1232  if (ifarg(5)) {
1233  w = vector_arg(5);
1234  } else {
1235  w = new Vect(x->size());
1236  std::fill(w->begin(), w->end(), 1);
1237  d = true;
1238  }
1239 
1240  int points = int((high - low) / step + .5);
1241  Vect* sum = new Vect(points, 0.);
1242 
1243  double svar = var / (step * step);
1244 
1245  // 4/28/93 ZFM: corrected bug: replaced svar w/ var in line below
1246  double scale = 1. / hoc_Sqrt(2. * PI * var);
1247 
1248  for (int i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
1249  double xv = int((x->elem(i) - low) / step);
1250  for (int j = 0; j < points; j++) {
1251  double arg = -(j - xv) * (j - xv) / (2. * svar);
1252  if (arg > -20.)
1253  sum->elem(j) += hoc_Exp(arg) * scale * w->elem(i);
1254  }
1255  }
1256  if (d) {
1257  delete w;
1258  }
1259  return sum->temp_objvar();
1260 }

1262 static Object** v_smhist(void* v) {
1263  Vect* v1 = (Vect*) v;
1264 
1265  Vect* data = vector_arg(1);
1266 
1267  double start = *getarg(2);
1268  int size = int(*getarg(3));
1269  double step = chkarg(4, 1.e-99, 1.e99);
1270  double var = chkarg(5, 0, 1.e99);
1271 
1272  int weight, i;
1273  Vect* w;
1274 
1275  if (ifarg(6)) {
1276  w = vector_arg(6);
1277  if (w->size() != data->size()) {
1278  hoc_execerror("Vector.smhist: weight Vector must be same size as source Vector.", 0);
1279  }
1280  weight = 1;
1281  } else {
1282  weight = 0;
1283  }
1284 
1285 
1286  // ready a gaussian to convolve
1287  double svar = 2 * var / (step * step);
1288  double scale = 1 / hoc_Sqrt(2. * PI * var);
1289 
1290  int g2 = int(sqrt(10 * svar));
1291  int g = g2 * 2 + 1;
1292 
1293  int n = 1;
1294  while (n < size + g)
1295  n *= 2;
1296 
1297  double* gauss = (double*) calloc(n, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
1298 
1299  for (i = 0; i <= g2; i++)
1300  gauss[i] = scale * hoc_Exp(-i * i / svar);
1301  for (i = 1; i <= g2; i++)
1302  gauss[g - i] = scale * hoc_Exp(-i * i / svar);
1303 
1304  // put the data into a time series
1305  double* series = (double*) calloc(n, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
1306 
1307  double high = start + n * step;
1308  if (weight) {
1309  for (i = 0; i < data->size(); i++) {
1310  if (data->elem(i) >= start && data->elem(i) < high) {
1311  series[int((data->elem(i) - start) / step)] += w->elem(i);
1312  }
1313  }
1314  } else {
1315  for (i = 0; i < data->size(); i++) {
1316  if (data->elem(i) >= start && data->elem(i) < high) {
1317  series[int((data->elem(i) - start) / step)] += 1.;
1318  }
1319  }
1320  }
1321 
1322  // ready the answer vector
1323  double* ans = (double*) calloc(2 * n, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
1324 
1325  // convolve
1326  nrn_convlv(series, n, gauss, g, 1, ans);
1327 
1328  // put the answer in the vector
1329  if (v1->size() != size)
1330  v1->resize(size);
1331  std::fill(v1->begin(), v1->end(), 0.);
1332  for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
1333  if (ans[i] > EPSILON)
1334  v1->elem(i) = ans[i];
1335 
1336  free(series);
1337  free(gauss);
1338  free(ans);
1339 
1340  return v1->temp_objvar();
1341 }

1496 static Object** v_copy(void* v) {
1497  Vect* y = (Vect*) v;
1498 
1499  Vect* x = vector_arg(1);
1500 
1501  int top = x->size() - 1;
1502  int srcstart = 0;
1503  int srcend = top;
1504  int srcinc = 1;
1505 
1506  int deststart = 0;
1507  int destinc = 1;
1508 
1509  if (ifarg(2) && hoc_is_object_arg(2)) {
1510  Vect* srcind = vector_arg(2);
1511  int ns = srcind->size();
1512  int nx = x->size();
1513  if (ifarg(3)) {
1514  Vect* destind = vector_arg(3);
1515  if (destind->size() < ns) {
1516  ns = destind->size();
1517  }
1518  int ny = y->size();
1519  for (int i = 0; i < ns; ++i) {
1520  int ix = (int) (srcind->elem(i) + hoc_epsilon);
1521  int iy = (int) (destind->elem(i) + hoc_epsilon);
1522  if (ix >= 0 && iy >= 0 && ix < nx && iy < ny) {
1523  y->elem(iy) = x->elem(ix);
1524  }
1525  }
1526  } else {
1527  if (y->size() < nx) {
1528  nx = y->size();
1529  }
1530  for (int i = 0; i < ns; ++i) {
1531  int ii = (int) (srcind->elem(i) + hoc_epsilon);
1532  if (ii >= 0 && ii < nx) {
1533  y->elem(ii) = x->elem(ii);
1534  }
1535  }
1536  }
1537  return y->temp_objvar();
1538  }
1539 
1540  if (ifarg(2) && !(ifarg(3))) {
1541  deststart = int(*getarg(2));
1542  } else {
1543  if (ifarg(4)) {
1544  deststart = int(*getarg(2));
1545  srcstart = int(chkarg(3, 0, top));
1546  srcend = int(chkarg(4, -1, top));
1547  if (ifarg(5)) {
1548  destinc = int(chkarg(5, 1, dmaxint_));
1549  srcinc = int(chkarg(6, 1, dmaxint_));
1550  }
1551  } else if (ifarg(3)) {
1552  srcstart = int(chkarg(2, 0, top));
1553  srcend = int(chkarg(3, -1, top));
1554  }
1555  }
1556  if (srcend == -1) {
1557  srcend = top;
1558  } else if (srcend < srcstart) {
1559  hoc_execerror("Vector.copy: src_end arg smaller than src_start", 0);
1560  }
1561  int size = (srcend - srcstart) / srcinc;
1562  size *= destinc;
1563  size += deststart + 1;
1564  if (y->size() < size) {
1565  y->resize(size);
1566  } else if (y->size() > size && !ifarg(2)) {
1567  y->resize(size);
1568  }
1569  int i, j;
1570  for (i = srcstart, j = deststart; i <= srcend; i += srcinc, j += destinc) {
1571  y->elem(j) = x->elem(i);
1572  }
1573 
1574  return y->temp_objvar();
1575 }

1644 static Object** v_interpolate(void* v) {
1645  Vect* yd = (Vect*) v;
1646  Vect* xd = vector_arg(1);
1647  Vect* xs = vector_arg(2);
1648  Vect* ys;
1649  int flag, is, id, nd, ns;
1650  double thet;
1651  ns = xs->size();
1652  nd = xd->size();
1653  if (ifarg(3)) {
1654  ys = vector_arg(3);
1655  flag = 0;
1656  } else {
1657  ys = new Vect(*yd);
1658  flag = 1;
1659  }
1660  yd->resize(nd);
1661  // before domain
1662  for (id = 0; id < nd && xd->elem(id) <= xs->elem(0); ++id) {
1663  yd->elem(id) = ys->elem(0);
1664  }
1665  // in domain
1666  for (is = 1; is < ns && id < nd; ++is) {
1667  if (xs->elem(is) <= xs->elem(is - 1)) {
1668  continue;
1669  }
1670  while (xd->elem(id) <= xs->elem(is)) {
1671  thet = (xd->elem(id) - xs->elem(is - 1)) / (xs->elem(is) - xs->elem(is - 1));
1672  yd->elem(id) = (1. - thet) * (ys->elem(is - 1)) + thet * (ys->elem(is));
1673  ++id;
1674  if (id >= nd) {
1675  break;
1676  }
1677  }
1678  }
1679  // after domain
1680  for (; id < nd; ++id) {
1681  yd->elem(id) = ys->elem(ns - 1);
1682  }
1683 
1684  if (flag) {
1685  delete ys;
1686  }
1687  return yd->temp_objvar();
1688 }

2427 /*=============================================================================
2428 
2429  FITTING A MULTIVARIABLE FUNCTION FROM DATA -- SIMPLEX METHOD
2430 
2431  double simplex( p,n,trial,a,b,c,d )
2432  double *p;
2433  vector of dimension n, containing variables
2434  int n;
2435  number of variables of the function to fit
2436  int trial;
2437  number of trials of simplex loop
2438  trial = 0: do simplex until the minimum pole has found
2439  trial > 0: do simplex [trial] times.
2440  double a,b,c,d
2441  values of contraction/expansion of the simplex;
2442  control the rate of the search in multidim variable space
2443  must be chosen by trial and error
2444  2.0, 1.4, 0.7, 0.3 -> standard values
2445 
2446  return most optimized eval value
2447  (negative if error occured)
2448 
2449  A function must be supplied by the user:
2450 
2451  external function DOUBLE EVAL(double *p);
2452 
2453  This function evaluates the mean square error between the
2454  the data and the multivariable function with the values of
2455  variables in vector p.
2456 
2457 =============================================================================*/
2458 
2459 
2460 #define SIMPLEX_MAXN 1e+300
2461 #define SIMPLEX_INORM 1.2
2462 
2463 /* 1.2: normal,
2464  1.3: extensive search,
2465  1.1: final adjustments
2466 */
2467 
2468 
2469 #define SIMPLEX_ALPHA 2.0
2470 #define SIMPLEX_BETA 1.4
2471 #define SIMPLEX_GAMMA 0.7
2472 #define SIMPLEX_DELTA 0.3
2473 
2474 /*
2475  values of contraction/expansion of the simplex;
2476  control the rate of the search in multidim variable space
2477  must be chosen by trial and error
2478  2.0, 1.4, 0.7, 0.3 -> standard values
2479 */
2480 
2481 static double splx_evl_;
2482 static int renew_;
2483 
2484 
2485 static double eval(double* p, int n, Vect* x, Vect* y, char* fcn) {
2486  double sq_err = 0.;
2487  double guess;
2488  int i;
2489  double dexp, t, amp1, tau1, amp2, tau2;
2490 
2491  if (!strcmp(fcn, "exp2")) {
2492  if (n < 4)
2493  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"exp2\") requires amp1,tau1,amp2,tau2");
2494  amp1 = p[0];
2495  tau1 = p[1];
2496  amp2 = p[2];
2497  tau2 = p[3];
2498 
2499  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2500  t = x->elem(i);
2501  dexp = amp1 * hoc_Exp(-t / tau1) + amp2 * hoc_Exp(-t / tau2);
2502  guess = dexp - y->elem(i);
2503  sq_err += guess * guess;
2504  }
2505  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "charging")) {
2506  if (n < 4)
2507  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"charging\") requires amp1,tau1,amp2,tau2");
2508  amp1 = p[0];
2509  tau1 = p[1];
2510  amp2 = p[2];
2511  tau2 = p[3];
2512 
2513  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2514  t = x->elem(i);
2515  dexp = amp1 * (1 - hoc_Exp(-t / tau1)) + amp2 * (1 - hoc_Exp(-t / tau2));
2516  guess = dexp - y->elem(i);
2517  sq_err += guess * guess;
2518  }
2519  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "exp1")) {
2520  if (n < 2)
2521  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"exp1\") requires amp,tau");
2522  amp1 = p[0];
2523  tau1 = p[1];
2524 
2525 
2526  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2527  t = x->elem(i);
2528  dexp = amp1 * hoc_Exp(-t / tau1);
2529  guess = dexp - y->elem(i);
2530  sq_err += guess * guess;
2531  }
2532  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "line")) {
2533  if (n < 2)
2534  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"line\") requires slope,intercept");
2535 
2536  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2537  guess = (p[0] * x->elem(i) + p[1]) - y->elem(i);
2538  sq_err += guess * guess;
2539  }
2540  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "quad")) {
2541  if (n < 3)
2542  hoc_execerror("Vector", ".fit(\"quad\") requires ax^2+bx+c");
2543 
2544  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2545  guess = (p[0] * x->elem(i) * x->elem(i) + p[1] * x->elem(i) + p[2]) - y->elem(i);
2546  sq_err += guess * guess;
2547  }
2548  } else {
2549  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2550  // first the independent variable
2551  hoc_pushx(x->elem(i));
2552  // then other parameters
2553  for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
2554  hoc_pushx(p[j]);
2555 
2556  guess = hoc_call_func(hoc_lookup(fcn), n + 1) - y->elem(i);
2557  sq_err += guess * guess;
2558  }
2559  }
2560  return sq_err / x->size();
2561 }

2564 static double eval_error(double* p, int n, Vect* x, Vect* y, char* fcn) {
2565  double retval;
2566 
2567  if (renew_ > 3 * (n + 1)) {
2568  retval = eval(p, n, x, y, fcn);
2569  if (retval == splx_evl_)
2570  return (splx_evl_);
2571  else
2572  return (SIMPLEX_MAXN);
2573  } else {
2574  retval = eval(p, n, x, y, fcn);
2575  if (splx_evl_ > retval)
2576  splx_evl_ = retval;
2577  return (retval);
2578  }
2579 }

2581 static double simplex(double* p, int n, Vect* x, Vect* y, char* fcn) {
2582  int i, j;
2583  int emaxp; /* max position */
2584  int eminp;
2585  int ptr;
2586 
2587  double* evortex; /* eval value of votexes */
2588  double* gvortex; /* the vector of gravity */
2589  double* vortex; /* parameter matrix */
2590  double* nvortex; /* new vortex */
2591  double emax;
2592  double emin;
2593  double fv1;
2594 
2595  evortex = (double*) calloc(n + 1, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
2596  gvortex = (double*) calloc(n, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
2597  vortex = (double*) calloc(n * (n + 1), (unsigned) sizeof(double));
2598  nvortex = (double*) calloc(n * 4, (unsigned) sizeof(double));
2599 
2600  if (0 == evortex || 0 == gvortex || 0 == vortex || 0 == nvortex) {
2601  Printf("allocation error in simplex()\n");
2602  nrn_exit(1);
2603  }
2604 
2605 
2606  // NEXT:;
2607  /* make the initial vortex matrix */
2608  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++) {
2609  for (j = 0; j < n; j++) {
2610  vortex[i * n + j] = p[j];
2611  if (i == j)
2612  vortex[i * n + j] *= SIMPLEX_INORM;
2613  }
2614  }
2615 
2616  /* evaluate the n+1 of vortexes and make the maximal one
2617  to be pointed out by emaxp */
2618  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++)
2619  evortex[i] = eval_error(&vortex[i * n], n, x, y, fcn);
2620 
2621 Label2:;
2622  emin = emax = evortex[0];
2623  emaxp = eminp = 0;
2624  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++) {
2625  fv1 = evortex[i];
2626  if (fv1 > emax) {
2627  emax = fv1;
2628  emaxp = i;
2629  }
2630  if (fv1 < emin) {
2631  emin = fv1;
2632  eminp = i;
2633  }
2634  }
2635  /* calculate the center of gravity */
2636  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2637  gvortex[i] = 0.0;
2638  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++)
2639  for (j = 0; j < n; j++)
2640  gvortex[j] += vortex[i * n + j];
2641  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2642  gvortex[i] = (gvortex[i] - vortex[emaxp * n + i]) / n;
2643 
2644  /* calculate the new vortexes */
2645 
2646  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2647  nvortex[i] = (1.0 - SIMPLEX_ALPHA) * vortex[emaxp * n + i] + SIMPLEX_ALPHA * gvortex[i];
2648  fv1 = eval_error(&nvortex[0], n, x, y, fcn);
2649  if (fv1 < evortex[emaxp]) {
2650  ptr = 0;
2651  goto UPDATE;
2652  }
2653 
2654  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2655  nvortex[1 * n + i] = (1.0 - SIMPLEX_BETA) * vortex[emaxp * n + i] +
2656  SIMPLEX_BETA * gvortex[i];
2657  fv1 = eval_error(&nvortex[1 * n], n, x, y, fcn);
2658  if (fv1 < evortex[emaxp]) {
2659  ptr = 1;
2660  goto UPDATE;
2661  }
2662 
2663  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2664  nvortex[2 * n + i] = (1.0 - SIMPLEX_GAMMA) * vortex[emaxp * n + i] +
2665  SIMPLEX_GAMMA * gvortex[i];
2666  fv1 = eval_error(&nvortex[2 * n], n, x, y, fcn);
2667  if (fv1 < evortex[emaxp]) {
2668  ptr = 2;
2669  goto UPDATE;
2670  }
2671 
2672  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2673  nvortex[3 * n + i] = (1.0 - SIMPLEX_DELTA) * vortex[emaxp * n + i] +
2674  SIMPLEX_DELTA * gvortex[i];
2675  fv1 = eval_error(&nvortex[3 * n], n, x, y, fcn);
2676  if (fv1 < evortex[emaxp]) {
2677  ptr = 3;
2678  goto UPDATE;
2679  }
2680 
2681  goto Label3;
2682 
2683 
2684 UPDATE:;
2685  /* update the vortex matrix */
2686  if (splx_evl_ == fv1)
2687  renew_++;
2688  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2689  vortex[emaxp * n + i] = nvortex[ptr * n + i];
2690  evortex[emaxp] = fv1;
2691  goto Label2;
2692 
2693 
2694 Label3:;
2695  /*
2696  ** search for the vortex that represents smallest eval vaule
2697  */
2698  emin = evortex[0];
2699  eminp = 0;
2700  for (i = 0; i < n + 1; i++) {
2701  if (evortex[i] < emin) {
2702  emin = evortex[i];
2703  eminp = i;
2704  }
2705  }
2706 
2707  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2708  p[i] = vortex[eminp * n + i];
2709  free(gvortex);
2710  free(evortex);
2711  free(vortex);
2712  free(nvortex);
2713  return (emin);
2714 }

2740 static double v_fit(void* v) {

2743  trial = 0: do simplex until the minimum pole has found
2744  trial > 0: do simplex [trial] times.

2779  // parameter value
2780  p[n] = *(p_ptr[n]);
2781  n++;

2801  }
2802  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "exp1")) {
2803  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {

2805  }
2806  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "line")) {
2807  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2808  fitted->elem(i) = p[0] * x->elem(i) + p[1];
2809  }
2810  } else if (!strcmp(fcn, "quad")) {
2811  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2812  fitted->elem(i) = p[0] * x->elem(i) * x->elem(i) + p[1] * x->elem(i) + p[2];
2813  }
2814  } else {
2815  for (i = 0; i < x->size(); i++) {
2816  hoc_pushx(x->elem(i));
2817  for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
2818  hoc_pushx(p[j]);
2819  fitted->elem(i) = hoc_call_func(hoc_lookup(fcn), n + 1);
2820  }
2821  }
2822

3246 
3247  for (int i = 0; i < l; i++) {
3248  int tr = int(trig->elem(i));
3249 
3250  // throw out events within the window size of the edges
3251  if (tr >= pre && tr < n - post) {
3252  trcount++;
3253  for (int j = -pre; j < post; j++) {
3254  avg->elem(j + pre) += data->elem(tr + j);
3255  }
3256  }
3257  }
3258  std::for_each(avg->begin(), avg->end(), [&](double& d) { d /= trcount; });
3259

3444 static Object** v_psth(void* v) {
3445  Vect* ans = (Vect*) v;
3446 
3447  // data set
3448  Vect* v1 = vector_arg(1);
3449 
3450  double dt = chkarg(2, 0, 9e99);
3451  double trials = chkarg(3, 0, 9e99);
3452  double size = chkarg(4, 0, v1->size() / 2);
3453  int n = int(v1->size());
3454 
3455  Vect* temp = new Vect(n);
3456 
3457  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
3458  int fj = 0;
3459  int bj = 0;
3460  double integral = v1->elem(i);
3461  while (integral < size) {
3462  if (i + fj < n - 1) {
3463  fj++;
3464  integral += v1->elem(i + fj);
3465  }
3466  if (i - bj > 0 && integral < size) {
3467  bj++;
3468  integral += v1->elem(i - bj);
3469  }
3470  }
3471  temp->elem(i) = integral / trials * 1000. / ((fj + bj + 1) * dt);
3472  }
3473 
3474  ans->vec().swap(temp->vec());
3475 
3476  delete temp;
3477 
3478  return ans->temp_objvar();

3481 static Object** v_inf(void* x) {
3482  Vect* V = (Vect*) x;
3483 
3484  // data set
3485  Vect* stim = vector_arg(1);
3486  int n = stim->size();
3487 
3488  double dt = chkarg(2, 1e-99, 9e99);
3489  double gl = *getarg(3);
3490  double el = *getarg(4);
3491  double cm = *getarg(5) / dt;
3492  double th = *getarg(6);
3493  double res = *getarg(7);
3494  double refp = 0;
3495  if (ifarg(8))
3496  refp = *getarg(8);
3497 
3498  if (V->size() != n)
3499  V->resize(n);
3500 
3501  double i = 0, v, ref = 0;
3502 
3503  V->elem(0) = el;
3504 
3505  for (int t = 0; t < n - 1; t++) {
3506  i = -gl * (V->elem(t) - el) + stim->elem(t);
3507  v = V->elem(t) + i / cm;
3508  if (v >= th && ref <= 0) {
3509  V->elem(t + 1) = 0;
3510  t = t + 1;
3511  V->elem(t + 1) = res;
3512  ref = refp;
3513  } else {
3514  ref = ref - dt;
3515  V->elem(t + 1) = v;
3516  }
3517  }

3521 static Object** v_pow(void* v) {
